He feels any attention to Sam Walton is to the individual and he prefers attention to Sam Walton (the founder of) the company, Shinkle said. He's ranked as the richest man in the nation by a leading business magazine, but to folks in Bentonville, a town of about 8700 people, Sam Walton is just another neighbor. He's just a part of the community, said Curt Loyd, executive director of the Bentonville Chamber of Commerce. He calls Bentonville home, and that is special to us. According to Forbes magazine's July 24 edition, the Walton family's estimated worth is $8. 